1. What is a Popup?
- A popup is an UI element that appears on top of the main page
- Types of popups:
    - Browser Window Popup(New Tab/Window)
    - Alert Popup
    - Model Popup(HTML-based popup)
    - Authentication Popup(Username/Password)

2. Window Popup (New Tab / Window)
- When clicking a button open a new browser Window or Tab
- Example:
    - Clicking "Login with google"
    - Payment gateway page

3. How Selenium Handles Window Popup
- Key Concept
    - Selenium uses window handle
        driver.current_window_handle -> Current window
        driver.windo_handles -> all windows
    
- Basic Example
    from selenium import webdriver
    from selenium.webdriver.common.by import By

    driver = webdriver.Firefox()
    driver.get("https://example.com")

    main_window=driver.current_window_handle
    driver.find_element(By.ID, "openWindow").click()
    windows = driver.window_handles
    for window in windows:
        if window!=main_window:
            driver.switch_to_windiw(window)
            break
        
    print(driver.title)
    driver.close() # close child-window
    driver.switch_to_window(main_window)

    - Important Methods
    Method & Use
    ------------
    - driver.switch_to_window -> Switch window
    - driver.close() -> close child window
    - driver.quit() -> Close all windows
    - driver.window_handles -> Get all windows

    - Advanced Window Handling
        - Multiple windows
        windows = driver.window_handles
        for window in windows:
            driver.switch_to_window(window)
            print(driver.title)
        
        - Switch by Title
        for window in driver.window_handles:
            driver.switch_to_window(window)
            if "Google" in driver.title:
                break
        
        - Wait for New Window
        from selenium.webdriver.support.ui import WebDriverWait
        from selenium.webdriver.support import expected_conditions as EC
        
        WebDriverWait(driver , 10).until(EC.number_of_windows_to_be(2))

4. Alert Popup (JavaScript Alert)
- Types:
    1. simple alert
    2. confirm alert
    3. prompt alert

- Simple Alert
    alert = driver.switch_to.alert
    alert.accept()   # OK
    alert.dismiss()  # Cancel

- Prompt Alert
    alert.send_keys("Hello")
    alert.accept()

- Get text
    print(alert.text)

5. Modal Popup (HTML Popup)
- Definition
    - Not a real browser popup
    - Just HTML +CSS overlay
    - Exists inside DOM
- Example:
    - Login modal
    - Signup modal

- Key Concept
    - NO switch_to
    - Handle like normal elements

- Example
    driver.find_element(By.ID, "openModal").click()
    driver.find_element(By.ID, "username").send_keys("test")
    driver.find_element(By.ID, "password").send_keys("1234")
    driver.find_element(By.ID, "loginBtn").click()
- Wait for Modal
    WebDriverWait(driver, 10).until(
    EC.visibility_of_element_located((By.ID, "modal"))
)

6. Authentication Popup
- Selenium Cannot handle OS-level popup
- Solution : URL Trick
    driver.get("https://username:password@example.com")

- Solution :
    AutoIT (Window)
    RobotClass (Java)

7. Difference: Window vs Modal
Feature & Window popup & Modal Popup
------------------------------------
- Type -> New browser window  , Inside DOM
- Switch -> YES , NO
- Selenium method -> switch_to_window , normal locators
- speed -> Slower, Faster


